         <abstract>
            <p>The authors carried out a numerical search for Fermat quotients Q&lt;sub&gt;a&lt;/sub&gt; = (a&lt;sup&gt;p - 1&lt;/sup&gt; - 1)/p vanishing mod p, for 1 ≤ a ≤ p - 1, up to &lt;latex&gt;$p &lt; 10^6$&lt;/latex&gt;. This article reports on the results and surveys the associated theoretical properties of Q&lt;sub&gt;a&lt;/sub&gt;. The approach of fixing the prime p rather than the base a leads to some aspects of the theory apparently not published before.</p>
          </abstract>
